The generated code will use AI APIs using Webdraw SDK

To use the SDK, import it like this.

import { getSDK } from "https://webdraw.com/webdraw-sdk"

inside of a <script type="module"

instantiates like this: const sdk = await getSDK()

And these are the APIs available:
type WebdrawSDK = {
  ai: {
    message: (chat: {
      messages: Array<{
        role: 'user' | 'assistant' | 'system';
        content: string;
      }>;
      system?: string;
      temperature?: number;
    }) => Promise<{
  id: string;
  type: "message";
  role: "assistant";
  model: string;
  content: Array<{
    type: "text";
    text: string;
  }>;
  stop_reason: "end_turn" | null;
  stop_sequence: null;
  usage: {
    input_tokens: number;
    cache_creation_input_tokens: number;
    cache_read_input_tokens: number;
    output_tokens: number;
  };
}>;
};

to call it, use it const response = await sdk.ai.message(...

If the required task is better suited with AI returning structured data,
use "tools" option from Claude API

This is a sample tool declaration

{
            name: "createFile",
            description: "Creates a file with the given name and content",
            input_schema: {
                type: "object",
                properties: {
                    filename: {
                        type: "string",
                        description: "Name of the file to create"
                    },
                    content: {
                        type: "string",
                        description: "Content of the file"
                    }
                },
                required: ["filename", "content"]
            }
        }

Remember to pass the schema in input_schema

This is an example return from the API:

{
    "id": "msg_01Gp4rD47wCbQytrtCkyGhjr",
    "type": "message",
    "role": "assistant",
    "model": "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vou ajudar vocÃª a gerar marcos para aterrar a linha vermelha. Vou criar uma sequÃªncia lÃ³gica de milestones para esse objetivo."
        },
        {
            "type": "tool_use",
            "id": "toolu_01JJkvKc2KG4xkGCRVgixNc3",
            "name": "generate_milestones",
            "input": {
                "milestones": [
                    {
                        "title": "AnÃ¡lise inicial da linha vermelha",
                        "duration": "1 semana",
                        "description": "Fazer levantamento "
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}

If the task requires image/file recognition, pass the file using the following example as format

[
  {
    "role": "user",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Below is the image of the drawing described above."
      },
      {
        "type": "image", // for png, jpg. Use "document" if it's a PDF
        "source": {
          "type": "base64",
          "data": "iVBORw0KGgoAA...",
          "media_type": "image/png"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
]

Don't send message with role: "system" so the API doesn't return this error:
Unexpected role \"system\". The Messages API accepts a top-level `system` parameter, not \"system\" as an input message role.
