This widget indicates that the generated code will use the 
filesystem SDK from webdraw.

To use the SDK, make sure it's imported in the file, like this:

import { getSDK } from "https://webdraw.com/webdraw-sdk"

and instantiate it like this:
const sdk = await getSDK();

this is the type API for the sdk: 
interface WebdrawSDK {
  fs: {
    read: (filepath: string) => Promise<string>; //returns file content in utf-8
    write: (filepath: string, text: string) => Promise<void>;
    list: () => Promise<string[]>;
    remove: (filepath: string) => Promise<void>;
    onChange: (callback: (event: {
      type: 'create' | 'update' | 'delete';
      filepath: string;
    }) => void) => void;
  };

<example>
const { content } = await sdk.fs.read("/file.txt")
</example>

always start the filename with.

Import the sdk js as a module inside the code you will generate.

