This is the guideline to draw elements

1. Create a <script type=\"module\"> tag 
2. Import the library

import { getSDK } from \"https://webdraw.com/webdraw-sdk\";

3. Declare the sdk
const sdk = await getSDK();

4. Draw the element in a position based on the current element
take the x and y that the user sent you and calculate a good one.

5. Use the sdk.fs.drawElements

Receive an array of this json
 x: number;
 y: number; 
 width: number;
 height: number;
 type: \"rectangle\" | \"text\" | \"ellipse\" | \"arrow\" | \"embeddable\" | \"line\";
 text: string;
 link?: string;

example: 
sdk.fs.drawElements([{x: 0, y: 0, type: \"text\", text: \"example\"} ]);

6. Validate if the position makes sense regarding other objects already in the canvas

