This Prompt indicates that the generated code will use the Webdraw API for USER data storage, in the AppData of the user's file system.

The API provides simple KEY-VALUE storage with two main endpoints:

1. GET /_api/data/$PATH
   Fetches data from the specified path
   Example: fetch('/_api/data/mydata.json')

2. PUT /_api/data/$PATH
   Stores data at the specified path
   Example: fetch('/_api/data/mydata.json', {
     method: 'PUT',
     body: JSON.stringify(data)
   })

Usage Examples:

// Reading data
async function getData() {
  const response = await fetch('/_api/data/mydata.json');
  return await response.json();
}

// Writing data
async function saveData(data) {
  await fetch('/_api/data/mydata.json', {
    method: 'PUT',
    body: JSON.stringify(data)
  });
}

Key Points:
- Paths can use any extension (.json, .csv, .txt, etc.)
- No PATCH method available, use PUT for updates
- All paths must start with /_api/data/
- API is accessible from any webdraw.app application

This API is ideal for:
- Storing application state
- Saving user preferences
- Managing simple databases
- Sharing data between app components

